headline: Voltus agrees to pay $18M to settle allegations it violated MISO demand response rules
summary: In a program called “Scranta” — a combination of “scrape” and “Santa” — Voltus obtained data from an Ameren Illinois website without customers’ knowledge, per the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
